( international ) france recommends the security council to strengthen nuclear inspection in iraq
xinhua news agency , united nations , february 11 ( reporter : guo lijun ) - the french delegation resident in united nations ( un ) has circulated an unofficial proposal to members of the security council on the 11th , which suggests to strengthen the nuclear weapon inspection in iraq .
france recommends to double the number of official weapons inspection personnel currently working in iraq within a short period of time . the number of weapons inspectors is to be further increased in stages thereafter until it reaches three times the current level .
at present , there are about 110 official inspection personnel in iraq .
france further proposes to &quot; freeze &quot; suspicious locations in iraq through better air surveillance or the use of united nations guards . furthermore , mobile customs inspection teams can be deployed to strengthen the inspection of goods imported by iraq .
france also recommends the establishment of a new intelligence agency in new york to coordinate the flow of intelligence from different countries to the un monitoring , verification and inspection commission and the international atomic energy agency .
the aforesaid two institutions should list out unfinished missions in the iraq disarmament according to priority sequence .
un is to post a liaison officer in iraq , who is responsible to communicate with iraqi officials on a daily basis .
france is circulating its proposal in a &quot; non-paper &quot; form .
actually , france and russia had expressed their point of views using this &quot; non-paper &quot; method during the exchange of views process for resolution 1441 .
according to the related regulation of the security council , this type of &quot; non-paper &quot; is less official than a draft resolution but can be elevated to a draft resolution on the request of the proposing country .
according to diplomatic circle here , france &apos;s proposal is similar in content to the speech given by french foreign minister , dominique de villepin , on the 5th after listening to u.s. secretary of state colin powell &apos;s intelligence briefing . this &quot; non-paper &quot; is a summary and an extract of france &apos;s point of view on the iraq problem made on request of some members of the security council .
( hong kong , macau and taiwan ) mainland china tourists have high spending power in macau
xinhua news agency , macau , february 14 ( reporter : li jie ) - in recent years , more and more mainland china tourists are visiting macau and their spending power is also increasing significantly .
according to statistics published by macau special administrative region government , foreign tourists spent 4.7 billion patacas in macau in the fourth quarter of last year and mainland china tourists accounted for 3.3 billion patacas making them the number one tourists group .
