euro-zone recorded a trade surplus of 102.3 billion euro last year
xinhua news agency , brussels , february 19 ( reporter : ping jian ) - according to the latest report from eurostat on the 19th , euro-zone external trade surplus in 2002 was 102.3 billion euro , a growth of more than 100 percent over the previous year thanks to a massive drop in import .
the statistic report indicated that trade surplus of the euro-zone in 2001 was 49.5 billion euro .
in last year , the trade surplus for the 15-member european union ( eu-15 ) was 6.1 billion euro .
the report said a massive drop in import was the main reason for the growth in trade surplus .
according to statistics , the import for the euro-zone and the whole european union had decreased by 4 percent over 2001 while export increased by 1 percent .
in the first eleven months of 2002 , eu-15 import from japan and u.s. decreased by 12 percent and 11 percent respectively , while export to japan and switzerland also decreased by 6 percent .
germany had a trade surplus of 117.9 billion euro , which was the largest trade surplus among all european union members . britain had a trade deficit of 63.6 billion euro , which was the largest deficit in the european union .
the number of financial crimes in shanghai , zhejiang and fujian dropped to a 13-year low
xinhua news agency , shanghai , february 20 ( reporter : wang hongyang ) - in 2002 , shanghai , zhejiang and fujian , the two provinces and one city situate at china &apos;s financial and trading hubs as well as at the forefront of the financial reform , had reported a 44.4 percent decrease in financial crimes over the previous year and amounts involved in the cases also decreased by 22.8 percent . actually , the number of cases has dropped to a 13-year low .
