( international ) austrian researchers found the spinal cells responsible for chronic pain
xinhua news agency , vienna , february 20 ( reporter : lin chuan ) - researchers from austria &apos;s university of vienna found a set of neuro-cells , which possesses long-lasting memory capability and shows a strong excitation on any slight pain stimulus . this could be another step forward for the identification of the causes of chronic pains .
sufferers of chronic pain are highly sensitive to pains and in the course of time , must endure pains in their daily lives .
however , people have little knowledge about the cause of this illness .
according to austria presse agentur , a team of researchers led by juergen sandkuehler , head of neurophysiology division , brain research institute , university of vienna , found that certain spinal cells had no unusual behavior under normal condition but showed excitation after pain stimulus in a tissue biopsy .
the stronger the pain stimulus is , the stronger the reaction .
however , they differ from other neuro-cells in that this set of spinal cells become over sensitive to pain stimulus . they break out even on the stimulus of insignificant pains .
researchers also found that spinal cells have a special channel . when the cells were stimulated , the channel would open , calcium ions poured in and triggered further chain reactions .
sandkuehler believed that the long-lasting memory of this type of spinal cells retains &quot; traces of pain &quot; and is the cause of over sensitive reaction to slight pains that chronic pain sufferers are experiencing .
he said the discovery could guide people to find methods to remove this type of memory .
china resident consumer price went up in january
xinhua news agency , beijing , february 21 ( reporter : liu dongkai ) - according to the monthly status report released by national bureau of statistics of china ( nbsc ) on the 21st , the overall level of china resident consumer price has increased by 0.4 percent in january over the same month last year . this is the first increase after a continuous 12 months decline on comparisons of prices with same month the previous year .
nbsc said this year &apos;s spring festival was at the end of january and was the main reason for an increase in the level of consumer price . last year , the spring festival was in february . as a result , the peak period of festival consumption occurred on different months and hence , the comparison was not a good indicator .
another reason was the colder weather this year .
among the 31 provinces , cities and autonomous regions surveyed , 22 showed an increase in the level of resident consumer price on comparison with same month last year while 7 had a decrease over same month last year .
statistics indicated a price increase in seasonal consumption items and services including fresh vegetables , fresh fruits , cultural entertainments etc . , while the price of items representing the long term consumption price trend , for example , food provisions and clothing etc. continued to show a decline trend .
a higher price in gasoline and diesel pushed up the price of liquefied petroleum gas and kept the costs on residential expenditures on an up trend .
china released the first sex education television series for junior and high school
